# Dependencies

Never add or install packages without explicit user approval.

## Ask first

- Proposing a new dependency (`pnpm add`, `pnpm add -D`, etc.)
- Running install commands that add packages to `package.json`
- Replacing or upgrading a dependency to a different package

When a dependency seems necessary, explain why, name the package(s), and wait for approval before running any install command.

## Allowed without asking

- `pnpm install` to install from the existing lockfile (no new packages)
- Using dependencies already listed in `package.json`

## Do not

- Run `pnpm add`, `npm install <pkg>`, or `yarn add` unless the user explicitly approved it
- Modify `package.json` or `pnpm-lock.yaml` to add dependencies on your own
